CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1956, pg. A18 reads: "Hazel Garland Honored - The Courier's Hazel Garland, flanked by Elaine Gaither, left, and Mrs. Clara E. Ingram, right, is surrounded by other members of the Junior Missionary Society of Bethlehem Baptist Church, McKeesport, who honored her at a tea last Sunday. Standing, left to right, Rita Brownfield, Shirley Johnson, Louise Moore, Adrianne Cole, president; Rosalyn McPherson, Mrs. Julia Brown, Cora Morgan and Vonceil Bell.  Mrs. Ingram and Mrs. Brown are advisers to the group. - "Teenie" Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Members of Junior Missionary Society, seated from left: Elaine Gaither, Hazel Garland, Clara E. Ingram; standing: Rita Brownfield, Shirley Johnson, Louise Moore, Adrianne Cole, Rosalyn McPherson, Julia Brown, Cora Morgan, and Vonceil Bell, gathered in Bethlehem Baptist Church for honorary tea, McKeesport
